OWASP Top 10 – Security Learning Log (THM)
Overview

This repository documents my hands-on learning progress on web application security concepts using TryHackMe, aligned with the OWASP Top 10 (2025).

Topics Covered

AS02: Security Misconfigurations
Identified risks caused by improper system and application configurations
Learned impact of default credentials, exposed services, and verbose error messages
Practiced recognizing insecure deployment setups

AS03: Software Supply Chain Failures
Understood risks from third-party dependencies and external components
Explored dependency vulnerabilities and package integrity issues
Learned importance of version control, patching, and trusted sources

AS04: Cryptographic Failures
Studied weak or improper use of cryptography
Identified risks such as plaintext data exposure and weak encryption algorithms
Practiced secure data handling and encryption basics

AS06: Insecure Design
Learned about flaws originating from poor system design decisions
Understood threat modeling and secure architecture principles
Identified logic flaws and missing security controls early in development

Key Takeaways
Security must be integrated at design, development, and deployment stages
Misconfigurations and weak cryptography remain common real-world risks
Dependency management is critical in modern applications
Secure design reduces vulnerabilities before implementation

